result.execSummary:
The defendant Sierra Jo Wiswell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Evenson. ADA: Matthew L Hartung DF ATTY: Donald J. Schwab DF: Sierra Jo Wiswell appeared. Case called at 10:45. Includes 14CF345, 14CF539. ADA Hartung updates the court.   Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads  G to amended Ct 1 to possession of methamphetamine  in 14CF345 and amended charge in 14CF539 to misdemeanor bail jumping. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of amended Ct 1  in 14CF345 and amended 14CF539. On motion of the State without objection , Crt reads in and dismisses with prejudice Ct 2 and 3 in 14CF345.  Court orders a compass evaluation. Bond continues. DE to be tested before leaving today. DE to make an appt. with Mr. O'Keefe today before leaving.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 5, 2015 at 10:30 am.

*AMENDED*

Includes 14CF345 and 14CF539

Bond on file

-It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations,  Kirk L.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

-Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

-Testing upon reasonable suspicion or the Courts directive.

-Defendant to reside with her Mother and or grandmother and follow her rules of the home.

-10:00 p.m. curfew.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
